result.execSummary: Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Joshua P. Hilt

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: of Atty's Fees...$149.50 to Atty Viney

Defendant Joshua P. Hilt in court with attorney Joseph L Viney as standby counsel.  Defendant Joshua P. Hilt in custody.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and State states appearances.  Court notes he has reviewed report from Dr. Engen.  DE states he hasn't received the report from the doctor.  Atty Viney speaks w/the DE off the record.  Back on the record, the Court sums up the doctor's report.  State feels DE is not competent and cannot become competent so they would be discharging the DE.  DE isn't objecting.  Court finds DE is not competent to proceed at this time and it's unlikely he will become competent so the DE would be discharged and the DE would be released.  The Court so orders.
Evidentiary hearing on April 4, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
Status hearing on April 12, 2016 at 08:00 am.

Defendant Joshua P. Hilt appeared by video means with Attorney Raabe, however Attorney Raabe advises defendant wishes to represent himself.  Prosecuting Atty Sue Mueller appeared for State of Wisconsin.  State request $150.00 cash bond w/ conditions.  Defendant waives reading of complaint.  Advised rights to an attorney.  File set for pre-trial conference/return date. $150.00 CASH bond set.  Special bond conditions as follows:  No contact with Starbucks WI Dells or Lake Delton, WI.

Attorney Raabe gives status of defendant's competency.  State agrees and request competency evaluation.  Matter recalled at 3:12 p.m.  Defendant has been removed from LEC holding.  Order for Competency signed and to be sent to DHS.  Dept to determine whether exam will be in-patient or out-patient basis.
Initial appearance on March 10, 2016 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Joshua P. Hilt not in court.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Raabe advised court defendant was speaking with private counsel by phone and matter will be adj. to tomorrow, March 10, 2016.  Court finds probable cause and finds good cause for adj. initial appearance.
